ML Book Reviews Classification

üìå Project Overview

This project is a machine learning model that classifies book reviews as either positive or negative using a pre-trained BERT model from Hugging Face.

üöÄ Technologies Used

Python

Hugging Face Transformers

Datasets (Hugging Face)

PyTorch

üìÅ Project Structure

- model/                # Saved fine-tuned model and tokenizer
- results/              # Training results and logs
- logs/                 # Training logs
- ML_Book_Reviews_Classification.py  # Main training script
- README.md             # Project documentation

‚ö° How to Run

Clone the repository:

git clone [REPOSITORY_URL]
cd ML_Book_Reviews_Classification

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the training script:

python ML_Book_Reviews_Classification.py

The trained model will be saved in the model/ directory.

‚úÖ Usage

To use the trained model for prediction:

from transformers import BertTokenizer, BertForSequenceClassification
import torch

model = BertForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained('./model')
tokenizer = BertTokenizer.from_pretrained('./model')

text = "This book is amazing!"
inputs = tokenizer(text, return_tensors='pt')
outputs = model(**inputs)
logits = outputs.logits
prediction = torch.argmax(logits, dim=1).item()
print("Positive" if prediction == 1 else "Negative")
